"25:1:3" : {s: 25, a: 1, w: 3, r: "نزل", t: "نَزَّلَ", l: "نَزَّلَ", lc: 62, tl: "liyakūna", lb: "ধাপে ধাপে অবতীর্ণ করা, ধাপে ধাপে প্রকাশ করা",e: "that he may be", b: "নাযিল করেছেন", i: "agar dia menjadi", f: 11, rm: "to descend, come down, go down, happen, alight at, settle in a place, lodge. anzala - to send down, give. nazulun - that which is prepared for a guests entertainment, abode, gift. manzil - mansion, station. nazzala - to cause to descend, send down. tanziil - sending down, divine revelation, orderly arrangement and authentic compilation, gradual revelation."},
"25:1:4" : {s: 25, a: 1, w: 4, r: "فرق", t: "ٱلْفُرْقَانَ", l: "فُرْقَان", lc: 7, tl: "lil'ʿālamīna", lb: "পার্থক্যকারী",e: "to the worlds", b: "সত্য মিথ্যার স্পষ্ট পার্থক্যকারী", i: "bagi seluruh alam", f: 3, rm: "to separate/distinguish/divide/split/decide. farqun - the act of distinction or separating. fariq - who separates, discriminates. firqun - separate part, heap. firqatun - band of human beings. fariqun - part/portion, some party or band of human beings. furqan - criterion of right or wrong, draft, evidence or demonstration, a name of The Quran, aid, victory, argument, proof, dawn, distinction."},
